{"author":{"id":"ab495368f431cbc3ee3dfc99ecf12eeb8b429836cb37bed3d5a1646d08668d30"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1685387596,"nonce":"x1jcqF+9SmzMFbKm1aJF2QA186o=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s5nL0T3","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/5331","origin":"github"},"title":"plink association analysis demands to set lambda value","message":"Hello!\nTo perform association analysis by galaxy's plink it's necessary to set \"lambda value\" option. When this field is skipped I have the following error: \"Error: Missing --lambda parameter\", because --lambda option is there by default. By contrast, the command line plink version doesn't force to set lambda value. It can be tricky to find the optimal value.The documentation for plink says: \"By default, the genomic control lambda is estimated from the data\".\nI think it would be more convenient if lambda value was an optional parameter.","files":null}]}